Earlier this week, the group kidnapped an Ethiopian businessman and held him captive in a house in Kensington for two days. JOHANNESBURG - Gauteng police have arrested three men believed to be part of a syndicate involved in robbing and kidnapping business people. Earlier this week, the group kidnapped an Ethiopian businessman and held him captive in a house in Kensington for two days. It s understood they demanded a ransom from his family for his safe return.The police's Lungelo Dlamini says the arrests come after several leads. He was taken from the OR Tambo International Airport to a house in Kensington and while he was being held up, the suspects used his cards to buy luxuries, including jewellery. 